Today is Friday Feb 26 the 57th day of 1988 There are 309 
days left in the year 
Todays Highlight in History 
On Feb 26 1919 Congress established Grand Canyon National 
Park in Arizona 
On this date 
In 1802 one of the great figures of French literature Victor 
Hugo was born in Besancon 
In 1815 Napoleon Bonaparte escaped from the Island of Elba to 
begin his second conquest of France 
In 1846 Buffalo Bill Cody was born near Davenport Iowa 
In 1848 the Second French Republic was proclaimed 
In 1870 the first New York City subway line was opened to the 
public 
In 1942 during World War II Navy flier Donald F Mason sent a 
fourword message from the Pacific to the US Navy in Washington 
Sighted sub sank same 
In 1951 the 22nd Amendment to the Constitution was ratified 
limiting a President to two terms in office 
In 1952 Prime Minister Winston S Churchill announced that 
Britain had developed its own atomic bomb 
In 1962 after becoming the first American to orbit the Earth 
John Glenn told a joint meeting of Congress exploration and the 
pursuit of knowledge have always paid dividends in the long run 
Ten years ago Israels Cabinet voted to continue its limited 
policy of establishing settlements in occupied territories 
specifically authorizing three new settlements in the West Bank 
Five years ago Britains Queen Elizabeth II and her husband 
Prince Philip arrived in San Diego Bay for a 10day West Coast 
tour that included a Hollywood banquet and visits with President 
Reagan and his wife Nancy 
One year ago The Tower commission appointed by President 
Reagan to probe the IranContra affair issued its report which 
rebuked the president for failing to control his national security 
staff 
Todays Birthdays Actor Mason Adams is 69 Actor Tony Randall 
is 68 Actress Betty Hutton is 67 Singer Fats Domino is 60 
Columnist Robert Novak is 57 Singer Johnny Cash is 56 
Thought for Today The secret of my success is that at an 
early age I discovered I was not God Oliver Wendell Holmes 
Jr US Supreme Court Justice 18411935 
